<h1 id="tagged-templates">Tagged templates</h1>
<p>Template strings can be &quot;tagged&quot; by putting a function before it.</p>
<pre><code class="language-js">tpl `hello ${name}! I'm ${me}`
</code></pre>
<p><code>tpl</code> is a function you write. It will be invoked like so:</p>
<pre><code class="language-js">function tpl (strings, values) {
  strings //=&gt; ['hello ', &quot;! I'm&quot;, '']
  values  //=&gt; [name, me]
}
</code></pre>
<p>While this is not used very often, it lets us write template engines.</p>
